&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deputy Ward Manger&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit a Deputy Ward Manager to join our Emergency Assessment Unit at Sunderland Royal Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EAU is a 27 bedded / unit who are based within the footprint of Emergency Care. The unit works very closely with the Emergency Department caring for a variety of patients in an acute short stay environment. You will be responsible for the day to day co-ordination of the unit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The unit is looking for highly motivated nurses who are passionate about delivering high quality care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part of the role involves co-ordinating the flow of patients from ED to EAU and onto their specialty wards, alongside ensuring that patients receive timely and safe effective care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will be a registered nurse with the following: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;• Excellent communication skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;• Excellent management and leadership skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;• experience at band 5 level in an acute medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;• A willingness to work flexibly in response to changing circumstances&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;• A good understanding of the goals and strategic direction of emergency and urgent care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;• Evidence of Continuous professional development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Degree level study or evidence of working towards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 hours per week and must be flexible to the needs of the service. The successful post holder will complete rotations to cover both day and night duties&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
